  "text": "Consumption of this beverage is traditionally believed to have a cooling effect on the body (especially in tropical weather) and is assumed to promote relaxation effects. Besides, dried longan fruits are a good source of vitamins (mainly vitamin C, app. 28 mg/100 g f.w.), antioxidants, minerals, and protein (5 g/100 g f.w.). Longan fruit extract is reported to exhibit rich antioxidant, antityrosinase, and anticancer activities [CITATION_1] . In traditional Chinese medicine, regular intake of longan fruits is believed to improve skin health and promote better cardiovascular system. So also, the use of screw pine leaves is also known to impart health benefits such as relief from pain (head, ear, stomach cramps) and reduce high fever and laxative effects.",
